<div><h3>MSCS 3021 - Human Computer Interaction </h3>  <hr>A survey of human-computer interaction (HCI) concepts, theory, and practice. Basic components of human-computer interaction. How to take a user-oriented perspective, rather than system-oriented. Design guidelines, evaluation methods, participatory design, communication between users, and system developers.<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Annually<br><br></div>		</td>
